<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>We need spell resist data for GZ - he says it's a non issue</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:06 p.m. 22/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> We need spell resist data for GZ - he says it's a non issue<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>According to Geoffrey Z, the spell resistance gains from one level to the next are trivial and should not be a factor. It's up to us to run some serious tests then and post our results so he can see if and where there are problems. Please test various offensive spells against targets 1-4 levels above yourselves and track the number of times your opponent resists the spell, and the amount of damage inflicted by the spell. Please cast the spell against the same target numerous times, as just casting it a few times is not a significant test given the random factors involved. Please don't flame, just get the test results we need to confirm whether or not there is a problem.
<P>Also, any interested in testing attack and damage differences between levels we need this data as well. Record the ATK, DAM, AC, STATS, and weapons used for both players involved in the combat. It would be nice to see some tests that involve two players of varying levels that had the same or very close ATK and AC numbers. Thanks for the help spellcasters.
<P>Here is GZ's reply on spell resistance and PVP:
<P>====================================================================================================
<P>I don't know what you guys are so upset about - the % that somebody +-3 levels get on resistance are trivial.
<P>I mean, they really are.
<P>Geoffrey C. Zatkin
<P>Arch-Magi of Norrath
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
